will be powered by diesel inboard engines and have a more robust hull construction appropriate to open water use. a previous craft of similar specification was withdrawn from this route as operations could not be sustained in competition with the lower cost base alternatives. two of the light duty craft have already sunk whilst carrying passengers, fortunately they had not yet entered open waters at the time, fortunately nearby assistance was available and there were no fatalities. there are also public ferries from lembar, lombok, to padang bai every few hours, with the trip taking around 3 to 4 hours. 